com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface Time


  • public interface Time
    The UPA Time type allows for bandwidth optimized representation of a time value containing hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond, and nanosecond information. Time is always represented as GMT unless otherwise specified.

      • blank

        void blank()
        Sets all members in Time to the values used to signify blank. A blank Time contains hour, minute, and second values of 255 and a millisecond value of 65535.

      • isBlank

        boolean isBlank()
        Returns true if all members in Time are set to the values used to signify blank. A blank Time contains hour, minute, and second values of 255 and a millisecond value of 65535.
        Returns:
        true if blank, false otherwise

      • isValid

        boolean isValid()
        Verifies contents of populated Time structure. Validates the ranges of the hour, minute, second, and millisecond members. If Time is blank or valid, true is returned; false otherwise.
        Returns:
        true if valid, false otherwise
